$ Excel function: offset

The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions[worksheet function] `offset()` returns a reference to a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[range] that is offset from a specific address
by a given amount of rows and columns.

{ Simple example

  In the following simple example, `=offset(b2, 3, 2)` returns `4 - 3` because this is the value that
  is found by going from `b2` three rows down and 2 columns to the right.
  -
  Similarly, the next `offset` function returns `5 - 4` because the `offset` is now started one row and one cell down and right, respectively.

  gh|about-Excel|/functions/offset/simple.bas||

  gh|about-Excel|/functions/offset/img/simple.png||
}

